"{\"uid\": \"cyclingnews.com-features-great-britains-cycling-hopes-for-the-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  Team GB heads to the 2024 Games with titles to defend and new talents looking to make their mark  When you purchase through links on our site, we may earn an affiliate commission.Here's how it works.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 201, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"-  The latest race content, interviews, features, reviews and expert buying guides, direct to your inbox!\", \"from\": 203, \"to\": 308, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You are now subscribed  Your newsletter sign-up was successful  Great Britain go into the2024 Olympic Gameslooking to uphold their status as the preeminent track cycling nation of the 21st century, having topped the medal table at every Olympics since their ground-breaking display in Beijing in 2008.\", \"from\": 310, \"to\": 611, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 374, \"end\": 387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.8763896675678795, \"rank\": 0.14104494488135666, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 595, \"end\": 602, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0204525567334108e-21, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Britain as a sporting nation had a middling Olympic pedigree until that point but a revolution in the funding system has heralded a gold rush, with GB finishing no lower than fourth in the overall medal table from Beijing onwards.\", \"from\": 613, \"to\": 843, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 613, \"end\": 620, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9999999843521438, \"rank\": 1.5647843991284265e-08, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 761, \"end\": 763, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.999999998378371, \"rank\": 1.6212441173283851e-09, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 827, \"end\": 834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0204525567334108e-21, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cycling has been a central part of that era, and in particular track cycling, which offers a host of events - and therefore medals - and the sort of environment where equipment counts for a lot and the money could be used to win the technological arms race.\", \"from\": 844, \"to\": 1101, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They have also tasted success in the past four Games in road cycling, mountain bike, and BMX, albeit more sporadically.\", \"from\": 1102, \"to\": 1221, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1191, \"end\": 1194, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\", \"score\": 0.9999975676430518, \"rank\": 2.4316892166241877e-06, \"text\": \"BMX\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Given their potential across all these disciplines, Great Britain are the favourites to top the cycling medal table once again.\", \"from\": 1223, \"to\": 1350, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1275, \"end\": 1288, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.8763896675678795, \"rank\": 0.14104494488135666, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, they will face a tougher challenge than they have in a long while.\", \"from\": 1351, \"to\": 1426, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Tokyo Olympics in 2021 saw a narrowing of the gap, and the feeling is that other nations have steadily been catching up in that arms race, at the same time as many of the celebrities from the British Cycling golden age have moved on, and that's without mentioning the freak gardening accident that has robbed them of their best track rider for Paris.\", \"from\": 1427, \"to\": 1781, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1431, \"end\": 1445, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.462354537795796e-36, \"text\": \"Tokyo Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1623, \"end\": 1638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British Cycling\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\"}, {\"begin\": 1775, \"end\": 1780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.218279117632644e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here, we delve a little deeper into Great Britain's medal prospects for the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 1783, \"to\": 1874, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1819, \"end\": 1832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.8763896675678795, \"rank\": 0.14104494488135666, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Katie Archibald was the victim of that freak accident,tripping over a step in her garden and suffering a double leg break and torn ligaments.\", \"from\": 1876, \"to\": 2017, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1876, \"end\": 1891, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Archibald\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Archibald\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Archibald\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Archibald\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Scot would have competed in the Omnium, Madison, and Team Pursuit, three disciplines in which she has previously been world champion.\", \"from\": 2018, \"to\": 2155, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2054, \"end\": 2060, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omnium\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.771282395228284e-55, \"text\": \"Omnium\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omnium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omnium\"}, {\"begin\": 2062, \"end\": 2069, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.723080400689747e-13, \"text\": \"Madison\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\"}, {\"begin\": 2075, \"end\": 2087, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_pursuit\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9373803622386882e-63, \"text\": \"Team Pursuit\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_pursuit\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_pursuit\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She won Olympic gold in the Team Pursuit in Rio in 2016 and the Madison in 2021, and was set to emerge from the shadow of the great Laura Kenny to take aim at the Omnium in Paris.\", \"from\": 2156, \"to\": 2335, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2184, \"end\": 2196, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_pursuit\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9373803622386882e-63, \"text\": \"Team Pursuit\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_pursuit\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_pursuit\"}, {\"begin\": 2200, \"end\": 2203, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.212944269938439e-25, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2220, \"end\": 2227, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.723080400689747e-13, \"text\": \"Madison\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\"}, {\"begin\": 2288, \"end\": 2299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Kenny\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laura Kenny\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Kenny\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Kenny\"}, {\"begin\": 2319, \"end\": 2325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omnium\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.771282395228284e-55, \"text\": \"Omnium\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omnium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omnium\"}, {\"begin\": 2329, \"end\": 2334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.218279117632644e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With a slew of medals across major competitions in recent years, Archibald has become arguably the world's best endurance track rider and there are no two ways about it, her absence is an absolute hammer blow for GB.\", \"from\": 2336, \"to\": 2552, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2401, \"end\": 2410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archibald_Prize\", \"score\": 0.999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.337284726230248e-12, \"text\": \"Archibald\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archibald_Prize\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archibald_Prize\"}, {\"begin\": 2549, \"end\": 2551, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.999999998378371, \"rank\": 1.6212441173283851e-09, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Still, there is a rising star who could be a household name by the end of the summer.\", \"from\": 2554, \"to\": 2639, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Emma Finucane is only 21 years of age but has burst onto the scene in the past couple of years, to the point where she won the Individual Sprint world title last autumn and added the European title in January.\", \"from\": 2640, \"to\": 2849, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2640, \"end\": 2644, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"score\": 0.8795006672364922, \"rank\": 0.13700880187592418, \"text\": \"Emma\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\"}, {\"begin\": 2778, \"end\": 2784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breeders'_Cup_Sprint\", \"score\": 0.9999995899380268, \"rank\": 4.1006190910920076e-07, \"text\": \"Sprint\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breeders'_Cup_Sprint\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breeders'_Cup_Sprint\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That'll be her big target here but she will also line up in the Keirin.\", \"from\": 2850, \"to\": 2921, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2914, \"end\": 2920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.270292555234541e-89, \"text\": \"Keirin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She's young but appears mature enough to handle this next step, and there is a real buzz around her heading into Paris.\", \"from\": 2922, \"to\": 3041, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3035, \"end\": 3040, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.218279117632644e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Finucane has breathed life into a women's sprint set-up that has never had the success of their women's endurance or men's sprint counterparts.\", \"from\": 3043, \"to\": 3186, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"GB have qualified for the Team Sprint in Paris for the first time since 2012, the failure ahead of Rio 2016 causing huge controversy and leading Katy Marchant to lash out at British Cycling management.\", \"from\": 3187, \"to\": 3388, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3213, \"end\": 3224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_sprint\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4541153483114586e-47, \"text\": \"Team Sprint\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_sprint\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_sprint\"}, {\"begin\": 3228, \"end\": 3233, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.218279117632644e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3332, \"end\": 3345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katy_Marchant\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katy Marchant\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katy_Marchant\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katy_Marchant\"}, {\"begin\": 3361, \"end\": 3376, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British Cycling\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Marchant returns for her third Olympics, as a mother and having acknowledged the culture change in the federation in recent years, while the sprint division is rounded out by 25-year-old Sophie Capewell.\", \"from\": 3389, \"to\": 3592, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3576, \"end\": 3591, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Capewell\", \"score\": 0.9999972463839808, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sophie Capewell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Capewell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Capewell\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Finucane and Capewell were in the trio that took silver at last year's Worlds, while Marchant joined at the Nations Cup in February to claim the first women's team sprint gold in any competition since 2012.\", \"from\": 3593, \"to\": 3799, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A medal will be the aim in Paris, and there is no reason it can not be gold.\", \"from\": 3800, \"to\": 3876, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3827, \"end\": 3832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.218279117632644e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As for how the women's endurance squad is shaping up without Archibald, the biggest name is that of Elinor Barker, who, like Marchant, is returning as a mother for her third Games.\", \"from\": 3878, \"to\": 4058, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3939, \"end\": 3948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archibald_Prize\", \"score\": 0.999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.337284726230248e-12, \"text\": \"Archibald\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archibald_Prize\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archibald_Prize\"}, {\"begin\": 3978, \"end\": 3991, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elinor_Barker\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elinor Barker\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elinor_Barker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elinor_Barker\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Barker was part of the all-conquering Team Pursuit squad of old and also has world titles to her name in the Points Race, Scratch Race, and Madison.\", \"from\": 4059, \"to\": 4207, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4097, \"end\": 4109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_pursuit\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9373803622386882e-63, \"text\": \"Team Pursuit\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_pursuit\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_pursuit\"}, {\"begin\": 4199, \"end\": 4206, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.723080400689747e-13, \"text\": \"Madison\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Barker looks set to replace Archibald in the Omnium while finding a new Madison partner in Neah Evans, although the pair have already teamed up at the European Championships.\", \"from\": 4208, \"to\": 4382, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4236, \"end\": 4245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archibald_Prize\", \"score\": 0.999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.337284726230248e-12, \"text\": \"Archibald\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archibald_Prize\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archibald_Prize\"}, {\"begin\": 4253, \"end\": 4259, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omnium\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.771282395228284e-55, \"text\": \"Omnium\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omnium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omnium\"}, {\"begin\": 4280, \"end\": 4287, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.723080400689747e-13, \"text\": \"Madison\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\"}, {\"begin\": 4299, \"end\": 4309, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neah_Evans\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Neah Evans\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neah_Evans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neah_Evans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both events represent medal opportunities even if gold is now less likely.\", \"from\": 4383, \"to\": 4457, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The same can be said for the Team Pursuit.\", \"from\": 4458, \"to\": 4500, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4487, \"end\": 4499, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_pursuit\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9373803622386882e-63, \"text\": \"Team Pursuit\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_pursuit\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_pursuit\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Josie Knight is the other familiar member of the quartet, while Anna Morris and Jess Roberts make their Olympic debuts, but Archibald is as good as irreplaceable.\", \"from\": 4501, \"to\": 4663, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4501, \"end\": 4513, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josie_Knight\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Josie Knight\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josie_Knight\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josie_Knight\"}, {\"begin\": 4565, \"end\": 4569, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Windass\", \"score\": 0.9545075725962421, \"rank\": 0.047602675975287646, \"text\": \"Anna\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Windass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Windass\"}, {\"begin\": 4570, \"end\": 4576, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morris_Motors\", \"score\": 0.9999999997799023, \"rank\": 2.035990571248838e-10, \"text\": \"Morris\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morris_Motors\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morris_Motors\"}, {\"begin\": 4625, \"end\": 4634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archibald_Prize\", \"score\": 0.999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.337284726230248e-12, \"text\": \"Archibald\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archibald_Prize\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archibald_Prize\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the men's side, the Team Pursuit is a big medal target and will be one of the most hotly-anticipated events of the entire Games.\", \"from\": 4667, \"to\": 4798, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4690, \"end\": 4702, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_pursuit\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9373803622386882e-63, \"text\": \"Team Pursuit\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_pursuit\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_pursuit\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Propelled by Dan Bigham,who has had a string of controversies with British Cyclingand worked behind the scenes for Denmark at the last Games, the group have breathed new life into an event where GB had slipped from their perch.\", \"from\": 4799, \"to\": 5026, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4866, \"end\": 4873, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9997391279773244, \"rank\": 0.00026087990042484243, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 4914, \"end\": 4921, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\", \"score\": 0.6015258995148368, \"rank\": 0.662438809045679, \"text\": \"Denmark\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\"}, {\"begin\": 4994, \"end\": 4996, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.999999998378371, \"rank\": 1.6212441173283851e-09, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WorldTour pros Ethan Vernon and Ethan Hayter are among the squad, along with an old Bigham ally in Charlie Tanfield and Ollie Wood.\", \"from\": 5027, \"to\": 5158, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5042, \"end\": 5054, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethan_Vernon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ethan Vernon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethan_Vernon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethan_Vernon\"}, {\"begin\": 5059, \"end\": 5071, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethan_Hayter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ethan Hayter\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethan_Hayter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethan_Hayter\"}, {\"begin\": 5126, \"end\": 5142, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlie_Tanfield\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Charlie Tanfield\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlie_Tanfield\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlie_Tanfield\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They clinched the world title at the 2022 World Championships, and although a crash wrecked their title defence, they claimed European gold with a time three seconds off the world record.\", \"from\": 5159, \"to\": 5346, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What makes GB's medal prospects uncertain, and the event so exciting, is the level of competition, with Bigham's former employers Denmark and Olympic champions Italy both involved in a contest that could come down to the wire.\", \"from\": 5347, \"to\": 5573, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5358, \"end\": 5360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.999999998378371, \"rank\": 1.6212441173283851e-09, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 5477, \"end\": 5484, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\", \"score\": 0.6015258995148368, \"rank\": 0.662438809045679, \"text\": \"Denmark\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\"}, {\"begin\": 5507, \"end\": 5512, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8694506458498353, \"rank\": 0.1423955163591112, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hayter has lost his way a little on the road with Ineos Grenadiers but appears at his natural best on the track.\", \"from\": 5575, \"to\": 5687, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5625, \"end\": 5641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ineos_Grenadiers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ineos Grenadiers\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ineos_Grenadiers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ineos_Grenadiers\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He will be in the hunt for gold in the Omnium, having become the European champion in January, and will link up with Ollie Wood in a dangerous pairing for the Madison.\", \"from\": 5688, \"to\": 5855, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5727, \"end\": 5733, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omnium\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.771282395228284e-55, \"text\": \"Omnium\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omnium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omnium\"}, {\"begin\": 5753, \"end\": 5770, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Athletics_Championships\", \"score\": 0.999999986981493, \"rank\": 1.3015859903994277e-08, \"text\": \"European champion\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Athletics_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Athletics_Championships\"}, {\"begin\": 5847, \"end\": 5854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.723080400689747e-13, \"text\": \"Madison\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the sprinting department, once ruled by some of Britain's most decorated Olympians in Chris Hoy and Jason Kenny, there are more muted expectations.\", \"from\": 5857, \"to\": 6007, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5908, \"end\": 5915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9999999843521438, \"rank\": 1.5647843991284265e-08, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 5946, \"end\": 5955, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chris Hoy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\"}, {\"begin\": 5960, \"end\": 5971, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason_Kenny\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jason Kenny\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason_Kenny\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason_Kenny\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tokyo silver and bronze medallist Jack Carlin leads the line alongside two debutants in Hamish Turnbull and Ed Lowe.\", \"from\": 6009, \"to\": 6125, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6009, \"end\": 6014, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999064320894714, \"rank\": 9.357666605295794e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 6043, \"end\": 6047, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Harkness\", \"score\": 0.6150808735729439, \"rank\": 0.6250908270474694, \"text\": \"Jack\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Harkness\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Harkness\"}, {\"begin\": 6048, \"end\": 6054, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8418006420036364e-15, \"text\": \"Carlin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\"}, {\"begin\": 6117, \"end\": 6124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ed_Lowe_(businessman)\", \"score\": 0.7159090621729652, \"rank\": 0.3968253968255327, \"text\": \"Ed Lowe\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ed_Lowe_(businessman)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ed_Lowe_(businessman)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As much as anything, it's the competition that counts against them.\", \"from\": 6126, \"to\": 6193, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Harrie Lavreysen has established himself as the thunder-thighed sprinting king and is the runaway favourite in the Individual Sprint and Keirin.\", \"from\": 6194, \"to\": 6338, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6194, \"end\": 6210, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harrie_Lavreysen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Harrie Lavreysen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harrie_Lavreysen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harrie_Lavreysen\"}, {\"begin\": 6320, \"end\": 6326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breeders'_Cup_Sprint\", \"score\": 0.9999995899380268, \"rank\": 4.1006190910920076e-07, \"text\": \"Sprint\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breeders'_Cup_Sprint\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breeders'_Cup_Sprint\"}, {\"begin\": 6331, \"end\": 6337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.270292555234541e-89, \"text\": \"Keirin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Likewise, his Dutch squad, along with the Australians, are expected to dominate the Team Sprint event.\", \"from\": 6339, \"to\": 6441, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6353, \"end\": 6358, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9999999650599426, \"rank\": 2.7487350628279597e-08, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 6423, \"end\": 6434, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_sprint\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4541153483114586e-47, \"text\": \"Team Sprint\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_sprint\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_sprint\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The bottom steps of the sprint podiums do look more open, so a medal is not out of the question if GB's riders get everything right on the day.\", \"from\": 6442, \"to\": 6585, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6541, \"end\": 6543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.999999998378371, \"rank\": 1.6212441173283851e-09, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite the inexperience, they do have an ace in the pack in that they are being coached by Jason Kenny, who managed to dismantle Lavreysen in the Keirin in Tokyo to become Britain's most decorated Olympian.\", \"from\": 6587, \"to\": 6794, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6679, \"end\": 6690, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason_Kenny\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jason Kenny\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason_Kenny\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason_Kenny\"}, {\"begin\": 6734, \"end\": 6740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.270292555234541e-89, \"text\": \"Keirin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\"}, {\"begin\": 6744, \"end\": 6749, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999064320894714, \"rank\": 9.357666605295794e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 6760, \"end\": 6767, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9999999843521438, \"rank\": 1.5647843991284265e-08, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 6785, \"end\": 6793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0245902130172756e-14, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the road, Britain have never hit the same heights as the track, which is perhaps unsurprising given the relative paucity of medals on offer and the overwhelming range of candidates for them.\", \"from\": 6798, \"to\": 6991, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6811, \"end\": 6818, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9999999843521438, \"rank\": 1.5647843991284265e-08, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nicole Cooke from 2008 is Britain's only road race champion and Bradley Wiggins from 2012 the only time trial champion.\", \"from\": 6992, \"to\": 7111, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6992, \"end\": 7004, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicole_Cooke\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nicole Cooke\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicole_Cooke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicole_Cooke\"}, {\"begin\": 7018, \"end\": 7025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9999999843521438, \"rank\": 1.5647843991284265e-08, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 7056, \"end\": 7071, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bradley_Wiggins\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bradley Wiggins\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bradley_Wiggins\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bradley_Wiggins\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Medals have been in short supply ever since.\", \"from\": 7112, \"to\": 7156, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In Paris, the biggest gold medal prospect on the road is surely Josh Tarling in the men's individual time trial.\", \"from\": 7158, \"to\": 7270, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7161, \"end\": 7166, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.218279117632644e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 7222, \"end\": 7226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\", \"score\": 0.9999998207413389, \"rank\": 1.7576256015967778e-07, \"text\": \"Josh\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Welshman is only 20 but has had an extraordinary debut two seasons as a professional, taking bronze at the World Championships last year and taking the European title soon after.\", \"from\": 7271, \"to\": 7453, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7271, \"end\": 7283, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Welshman_(newspaper)\", \"score\": 0.771426651535623, \"rank\": 0.29629629629633375, \"text\": \"The Welshman\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Welshman_(newspaper)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Welshman_(newspaper)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Earlier this year the Belgian star Wout van Aert was asked who the best time triallist in the world was.\", \"from\": 7454, \"to\": 7558, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7476, \"end\": 7483, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9999613255134133, \"rank\": 3.696277994569357e-05, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 7489, \"end\": 7502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wout_van_Aert\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wout van Aert\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wout_van_Aert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wout_van_Aert\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"For now, Evenepoel, but soon, Tarling,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 7559, \"to\": 7608, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This could be his moment.\", \"from\": 7609, \"to\": 7634, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The flat course in Paris suits him perfectly, although the same is true of the Hour Record holder Filippo Ganna, who might have a thing or two to say about Van Aert's comments.\", \"from\": 7635, \"to\": 7811, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7654, \"end\": 7659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.218279117632644e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 7733, \"end\": 7746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Filippo_Ganna\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Filippo Ganna\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Filippo_Ganna\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Filippo_Ganna\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ethan Hayter also lines up for GB and has the calibre for a strong result but Tarling is the medal contender and some would say the favourite for gold.\", \"from\": 7812, \"to\": 7963, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7812, \"end\": 7824, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethan_Hayter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ethan Hayter\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethan_Hayter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethan_Hayter\"}, {\"begin\": 7843, \"end\": 7845, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.999999998378371, \"rank\": 1.6212441173283851e-09, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As for the men's road race, it's much more of a lottery but in Tom Pidcock GB have a rider suited to the course and to the occasion, even if his early exit from the Tour de France with COVID-19 has left a question mark over his preparation.\", \"from\": 7967, \"to\": 8207, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8030, \"end\": 8041, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Pidcock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\"}, {\"begin\": 8042, \"end\": 8044, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.999999998378371, \"rank\": 1.6212441173283851e-09, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 8132, \"end\": 8146, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 0.9999999996007318, \"rank\": 3.9889735630433075e-10, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 8152, \"end\": 8160, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.972612901326293e-17, \"text\": \"COVID-19\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pidcock impressed from his debut in an elite World Champs as a 21-year-old and GB's best finisher in Imola in 2020.\", \"from\": 8208, \"to\": 8323, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8287, \"end\": 8289, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.999999998378371, \"rank\": 1.6212441173283851e-09, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 8309, \"end\": 8314, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imola_Circuit\", \"score\": 0.9999999999790816, \"rank\": 1.9988919589466408e-11, \"text\": \"Imola\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imola_Circuit\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imola_Circuit\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has since added Strade Bianche and Amstel Gold Race to a palmar\\u00e8s that is still being built in conjunction with other disciplines.\", \"from\": 8324, \"to\": 8457, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8343, \"end\": 8357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Strade_Bianche\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.154595263115003e-14, \"text\": \"Strade Bianche\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Strade_Bianche\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Strade_Bianche\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In fact, Pidcock is also the reigning Olympic champion in mountain bike and will be out to defend that title five days before the road race.\", \"from\": 8458, \"to\": 8598, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Fred Wright is a proven Tour of Flanders top-10 rider, Stevie Williams won Fl\\u00e8che Wallonne this spring, and Tarling can never be underestimated as he doubles up with the TT, but it's Pidcock who's realistically GB's leading light here.\", \"from\": 8599, \"to\": 8834, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8599, \"end\": 8610, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Wright_(cyclist)\", \"score\": 0.9999956969842781, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fred Wright\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Wright_(cyclist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Wright_(cyclist)\"}, {\"begin\": 8654, \"end\": 8669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stevie_Williams\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stevie Williams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stevie_Williams\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stevie_Williams\"}, {\"begin\": 8769, \"end\": 8771, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Man_TT\", \"score\": 0.99820326981176, \"rank\": 0.0017999642383815055, \"text\": \"TT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Man_TT\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Man_TT\"}, {\"begin\": 8810, \"end\": 8812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.999999998378371, \"rank\": 1.6212441173283851e-09, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You never know quite what you are going to get with the Yorkshireman, but when he strikes, he strikes big.\", \"from\": 8835, \"to\": 8941, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8891, \"end\": 8903, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yorkshire\", \"score\": 0.9999378597648683, \"rank\": 6.214409659463116e-05, \"text\": \"Yorkshireman\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yorkshire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yorkshire\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the women's side, Lizzie Deignan is Britain's big name, a former world champion, major Classics champion, and Olympic silver medallist from 2012.\", \"from\": 8943, \"to\": 9091, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8964, \"end\": 8978, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lizzie_Deignan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lizzie Deignan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lizzie_Deignan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lizzie_Deignan\"}, {\"begin\": 8982, \"end\": 8989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9999999843521438, \"rank\": 1.5647843991284265e-08, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 9033, \"end\": 9041, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Classic_cycle_races\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.03501069390613e-53, \"text\": \"Classics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Classic_cycle_races\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Classic_cycle_races\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She's now 35 and has not won a race since she landed the inaugural Paris-Roubaix Femmes in 2021, although she has always stepped up to the plate in international events, as recently as last year's Worlds, where she was sixth.\", \"from\": 9092, \"to\": 9317, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9159, \"end\": 9172, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\\u2013Roubaix\", \"score\": 0.9824390445527784, \"rank\": 0.004431782209560121, \"text\": \"Paris-Roubaix\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\\u2013Roubaix\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\\u2013Roubaix\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Deignan might well injure something but if represents more of the past, then the future appears to belong to Pfeiffer Georgi.\", \"from\": 9319, \"to\": 9444, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9319, \"end\": 9326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Herbert_Girton_Deignan\", \"score\": 0.9999999696428863, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Deignan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Herbert_Girton_Deignan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Herbert_Girton_Deignan\"}, {\"begin\": 9428, \"end\": 9443, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pfeiffer_Georgi\", \"score\": 0.9999994495557681, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pfeiffer Georgi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pfeiffer_Georgi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pfeiffer_Georgi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 23-year-old has really started to hit her stride now and still has bags of potential to explore.\", \"from\": 9445, \"to\": 9545, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She retained her British national champion's jersey last month, in a season in which she made a Classics breakthrough with a podium at Paris-Roubaix.\", \"from\": 9546, \"to\": 9695, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9563, \"end\": 9588, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Figure_Skating_Championships\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British national champion\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Figure_Skating_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Figure_Skating_Championships\"}, {\"begin\": 9642, \"end\": 9650, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Classic_cycle_races\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.03501069390613e-53, \"text\": \"Classics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Classic_cycle_races\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Classic_cycle_races\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She'd prefer the Olympics course to be a little flatter but then again she was also fourth in Amstel Gold this year.\", \"from\": 9696, \"to\": 9812, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Anna Henderson, the aerodynamic Visma-Lease a Bike rider, represents GB in the time trial, doubling up with the road race.\", \"from\": 9814, \"to\": 9936, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9814, \"end\": 9828, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Henderson\", \"score\": 0.9999958972005097, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anna Henderson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Henderson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Henderson\"}, {\"begin\": 9883, \"end\": 9885, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.999999998378371, \"rank\": 1.6212441173283851e-09, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She was fourth at last year's Worlds TT and second at the European Championships.\", \"from\": 9937, \"to\": 10018, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9974, \"end\": 9976, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Man_TT\", \"score\": 0.99820326981176, \"rank\": 0.0017999642383815055, \"text\": \"TT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Man_TT\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Man_TT\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Given the sheer depth of competition, a medal will be a tall order but she will want to be knocking on the door.\", \"from\": 10019, \"to\": 10131, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mountain biking was only added to the Olympic programme in 1996, with just the Cross-Country discipline included.\", \"from\": 10135, \"to\": 10248, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Britain had never won a medal until Tom Pidcock turned up in Tokyo and stormed off with gold, one of a number of breakthrough moments in his nascent career.\", \"from\": 10249, \"to\": 10405, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10249, \"end\": 10256, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9999999843521438, \"rank\": 1.5647843991284265e-08, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 10285, \"end\": 10296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Pidcock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\"}, {\"begin\": 10310, \"end\": 10315, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999064320894714, \"rank\": 9.357666605295794e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pidcock will be out to defend his title and will be the favourite for the gold medal in Paris.\", \"from\": 10407, \"to\": 10501, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10495, \"end\": 10500, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.218279117632644e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 24-year-old's efforts on the road and in cyclo-cross have not dampened his mountain biking talents - in fact, he has said he was 'born to mountain bike - and he has dipped in this season to take some commanding wins, notably at Nove Mesto and Crans Montana.\", \"from\": 10502, \"to\": 10763, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10755, \"end\": 10762, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montana\", \"score\": 0.9999962596036234, \"rank\": 3.723743517075443e-06, \"text\": \"Montana\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montana\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The legendary Nino Schurter, veteran of four Olympics and winner of one, will be among the contenders, as will his compatriot Mathias Fl\\u00fcckiger, but Pidcock on song has the beating of both.\", \"from\": 10764, \"to\": 10953, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10778, \"end\": 10791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nino_Schurter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nino Schurter\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nino_Schurter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nino_Schurter\"}, {\"begin\": 10890, \"end\": 10907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathias_Fl\\u00fcckiger\", \"score\": 0.9999996347315331, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mathias Fl\\u00fcckiger\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathias_Fl\\u00fcckiger\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathias_Fl\\u00fcckiger\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pidcock will be joined in the men's race by rising star Charlie Aldridge.\", \"from\": 10955, \"to\": 11028, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11019, \"end\": 11027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommy_Aldridge\", \"score\": 0.9974871169164787, \"rank\": 0.0025103428000071517, \"text\": \"Aldridge\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommy_Aldridge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommy_Aldridge\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A former world champion at junior and U23 level, he has only stepped up to the elites this season but placed an eye-catching fourth in Nove Mesto, which actually earned GB their second spot for Paris.\", \"from\": 11029, \"to\": 11229, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11067, \"end\": 11070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Under-20_athletics\", \"score\": 0.9149162725745608, \"rank\": 0.09297973290846423, \"text\": \"U23\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Under-20_athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Under-20_athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 11164, \"end\": 11174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nov\\u00e9_M\\u011bsto_na_Morav\\u011b\", \"score\": 0.8868360270686342, \"rank\": 0.12760416666661684, \"text\": \"Nove Mesto\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nov\\u00e9_M\\u011bsto_na_Morav\\u011b\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nov\\u00e9_M\\u011bsto_na_Morav\\u011b\"}, {\"begin\": 11198, \"end\": 11200, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.999999998378371, \"rank\": 1.6212441173283851e-09, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 11223, \"end\": 11228, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.218279117632644e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There'll be no expectations, but more than a little excitement over what he could achieve.\", \"from\": 11230, \"to\": 11320, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"GB have also qualified two riders for the women's race, making a full complement for the first time since Sydney in 2000.\", \"from\": 11322, \"to\": 11443, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11428, \"end\": 11434, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999999681249397, \"rank\": 3.187503100428375e-08, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Evie Richards, who was seventh in Tokyo three years ago before taking the world title, will lead the line but faces question marks over her form.\", \"from\": 11444, \"to\": 11589, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11444, \"end\": 11457, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evie_Richards\", \"score\": 0.9999999329947991, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Evie Richards\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evie_Richards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evie_Richards\"}, {\"begin\": 11478, \"end\": 11483, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999064320894714, \"rank\": 9.357666605295794e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She has had a season disrupted by injury, notably a concussion in the spring, and although hopes were raised by recent results - a podium in Crans Montana and sixth in Les Gets - she remains an outsider for a medal.\", \"from\": 11590, \"to\": 11805, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11737, \"end\": 11744, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montana\", \"score\": 0.9999962596036234, \"rank\": 3.723743517075443e-06, \"text\": \"Montana\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montana\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As in the men's race, the established campaigner will be joined by a rising star, in the form of Ella Maclean-Howell, who has got the nod for the second spot despite being just 19 years of age.\", \"from\": 11807, \"to\": 12000, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11904, \"end\": 11908, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ella_Fitzgerald\", \"score\": 0.9999999933124855, \"rank\": 6.6873469968603975e-09, \"text\": \"Ella\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ella_Fitzgerald\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ella_Fitzgerald\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The BMX was one of the feel-good areas for British Cycling in Toyko.\", \"from\": 12004, \"to\": 12072, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12008, \"end\": 12011, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\", \"score\": 0.9999975676430518, \"rank\": 2.4316892166241877e-06, \"text\": \"BMX\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\"}, {\"begin\": 12047, \"end\": 12062, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British Cycling\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Beth Shriever stormed to a stunning gold medal and her celebrations with Kye Whyte, who won a silver medal, will live long in the memory.\", \"from\": 12073, \"to\": 12210, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12146, \"end\": 12155, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kye_Whyte\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kye Whyte\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kye_Whyte\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kye_Whyte\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Together, they became GB's first ever Olympics BMX medallists, somewhat in spite of the system, which saw funding cuts that controversially were heaviest for the female riders.\", \"from\": 12211, \"to\": 12387, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12233, \"end\": 12235, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.999999998378371, \"rank\": 1.6212441173283851e-09, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 12258, \"end\": 12261, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\", \"score\": 0.9999975676430518, \"rank\": 2.4316892166241877e-06, \"text\": \"BMX\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Shriever and Whyte return to represent GB in Paris in the sole spots for the women's and men's BMX Racing events.\", \"from\": 12389, \"to\": 12502, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12428, \"end\": 12430, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.999999998378371, \"rank\": 1.6212441173283851e-09, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 12434, \"end\": 12439, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.218279117632644e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 12484, \"end\": 12487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\", \"score\": 0.9999975676430518, \"rank\": 2.4316892166241877e-06, \"text\": \"BMX\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Soon after that golden day in Tokyo, Shriever became the world champion, a title she reclaimed last autumn, confirming her status at the top of the sport.\", \"from\": 12503, \"to\": 12657, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12533, \"end\": 12538, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999064320894714, \"rank\": 9.357666605295794e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She suffered a collarbone fracture in May but says that will not affect her in Paris, having also dislocated a shoulder in the run-up to Tokyo.\", \"from\": 12658, \"to\": 12801, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12737, \"end\": 12742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.218279117632644e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 12795, \"end\": 12800, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999064320894714, \"rank\": 9.357666605295794e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now a fully-funded professional BMX rider, a second Olympic title would cement her greatness.\", \"from\": 12802, \"to\": 12895, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12834, \"end\": 12843, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\", \"score\": 0.9999998493576754, \"rank\": 1.506423007894058e-07, \"text\": \"BMX rider\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As for Whyte, he won his first World Cup event in February and even if he has not had a particularly strong or consistent campaign since then, he will feel he's capable of pulling something out of the bag on the day.\", \"from\": 12897, \"to\": 13113, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After all, there is a sense of unfinished business; he won silver as a 21-year-old in Tokyo, but felt it could and perhaps should have been gold.\", \"from\": 13114, \"to\": 13259, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13200, \"end\": 13205, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999064320894714, \"rank\": 9.357666605295794e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is also a Freestyle BMX discipline, which made its Olympic debut in Tokyo, and where GB could buttress their medal tally.\", \"from\": 13261, \"to\": 13388, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13277, \"end\": 13290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Freestyle_BMX\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Freestyle BMX\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Freestyle_BMX\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Freestyle_BMX\"}, {\"begin\": 13335, \"end\": 13340, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999064320894714, \"rank\": 9.357666605295794e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 13352, \"end\": 13354, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.999999998378371, \"rank\": 1.6212441173283851e-09, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Charlotte Worthington won the gold three years ago when she became the first-ever woman to land a 360 backflip.\", \"from\": 13389, \"to\": 13500, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13389, \"end\": 13410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Worthington\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Charlotte Worthington\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Worthington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Worthington\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She has admitted to struggling to adapt to that stardom, while the competition has become more intense, which is why expectations are a little more muted this time out.\", \"from\": 13501, \"to\": 13669, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kieran Reilly is the men's Freestyle rider, who has strong credentials after becoming World and European Champion last year.\", \"from\": 13671, \"to\": 13795, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13671, \"end\": 13677, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kieran_Culkin\", \"score\": 0.9997683829724348, \"rank\": 0.00023167068674897765, \"text\": \"Kieran\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kieran_Culkin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kieran_Culkin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He wasn't so dominant in qualifying, and Logan Martin remains the rider to beat, but he will be in the hunt for a medal.\", \"from\": 13796, \"to\": 13916, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13843, \"end\": 13849, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glenn_L._Martin_Company\", \"score\": 0.9999999998835847, \"rank\": 8.038514898676309e-11, \"text\": \"Martin\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glenn_L._Martin_Company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glenn_L._Martin_Company\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Patrick is an NCTJ-accredited journalist with a bachelor's degree in modern languages (French and Spanish) and a decade's experience in digital sports media, largely within the world of cycling.\", \"from\": 13922, \"to\": 14116, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13922, \"end\": 13929, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Star\", \"score\": 0.6917794104214643, \"rank\": 0.4433701935350872, \"text\": \"Patrick\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Star\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Star\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He re-joined Cyclingnews as Deputy Editor in February 2026, having previously spent eight years on staff between 2015 and 2023.\", \"from\": 14117, \"to\": 14244, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14130, \"end\": 14141, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cyclingnews\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In between, he was Deputy Editor at GCN and spent 18 months working across the sports portfolio at Future before returning to the cycling press pack.\", \"from\": 14245, \"to\": 14394, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14281, \"end\": 14284, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/GameCube\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9829217166570596e-23, \"text\": \"GCN\", \"types\": [\"Q1067263\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/GameCube\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/GameCube\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Patrick works across Cyclingnews' wide-ranging output, assisting the Editor in global content strategy, with a particular focus on shaping CN's news operation.\", \"from\": 14395, \"to\": 14554, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14395, \"end\": 14402, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Star\", \"score\": 0.6917794104214643, \"rank\": 0.4433701935350872, \"text\": \"Patrick\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Star\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Star\"}, {\"begin\": 14416, \"end\": 14427, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cyclingnews\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cyclingnews is part of Future plc, an international media group and leading digital publisher.Visit our corporate site.\", \"from\": 14556, \"to\": 14675, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14556, \"end\": 14567, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cyclingnews\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyclingnews.com\"}, {\"begin\": 14579, \"end\": 14589, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Future_plc\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Future plc\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Future_plc\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Future_plc\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9 Future Publishing Limited Quay House, The Ambury, Bath BA1 1UA.\", \"from\": 14677, \"to\": 14742, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14679, \"end\": 14696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Future_plc\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2498689747370386e-32, \"text\": \"Future Publis